# Cursor AI Mode Rules

- When using Composer 2.5, never use Fast mode.
- This rule is mandatory.
- The restriction is even stricter when using subagents.
- If subagent work is needed, ensure the session is not in Fast mode before starting.
- Do not suggest Fast mode as a shortcut for this repository.
- If there is any ambiguity about the active mode, assume Fast mode is disallowed and continue with a non-Fast workflow.

# Why

- This repository contains local automation code and UI behavior where low-context or rushed edits are more likely to create subtle breakage.
- Subagent work increases coordination complexity, so Fast mode is especially inappropriate there.
